<p>The Liberal government made deficits illegal in 2001:</p>

<blockquote>"The main estimates for a fiscal year must not contain a forecast of a deficit for that fiscal year."</blockquote>
<p><cite><a href="http://www.bclaws.ca/EPLibraries/bclaws_new/document/ID/freeside/00_01028_01#section2">BCLaws.ca</a></cite></p>

<p>Feb. 2 2009, that legislation was amended to allow them.</p>

<p>On the campaign trail:</p>

<blockquote>Clark has reiterated during her campaign her pledge to use the revenues from LNG to establish a Prosperity Fund to pay down the provincial debt in 15 years.</blockquote>
<p><cite><a href="http://www.vancouversun.com/news/bc-election/Clark+takes+campaign+heart+region/8263155/story.html">Vancouver Sun</a></cite>.</p>

<p>Amount of revenues from LNG sources so far? Zero.</p>

<p>Yeah, right.</p>

